Manufactured by [[Sienar Fleet Systems/Legends|Sienar Fleet Systems]],<ref name="DB" /> '''Black 4''' was a [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE/ln starfighter]] within the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]]. Armed with a pair of [[L-s1 laser cannon/Legends|L-s1 laser cannons]],<ref name="anh" /> The [[TIE series/Legends|TIE/LN]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] served in the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire's]] [[Black Squadron (Galactic Empire)/Legends|Black Squadron]]<ref name="B4card" /> by [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]]. By that [[Standard year/Legends|year]], it was operated by the [[TIE pilot]] [[DS-61-4]] and stationed on the Imperial [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|DS-1 Orbital Battle Station]]. Black 4's [[Cockpit/Legends|cockpit]] featured the standard wheel and yoke control system for TIE [[Pilot/Legends|pilots]].<ref name="anh" />

In 0 [[Galactic Standard Calendar|BBY]], the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] attacked the DS-1 Orbital Battle Station during the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]]. Black 4 was among the Black Squadron TIE/LN starfighters that attempted to defend the [[Space station/Legends|station]] from the Alliance starfighters. During the battle, Black 4 scored a direct hit on [[Rebel pilot/Legends|Rebel pilot]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]], who flew the [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wing]] [[Red Five/Legends|Red Five]]. Skywalker asked fellow Rebel pilot [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] for assistance, and Antilles successfully destroyed Black 4 and [[Death/Legends|killed]] DS-61-4.<ref name="anh" />

==Behind the scenes==
Black 4 first appeared in the [[1976]] [[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|novelization]] of the [[original trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']],<ref name="EP4NOVEL">[[Star Wars: A New Hope (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode IV: A New Hope'' novelization]]</ref> before appearing in the [[1977]] film itself,<ref name="anh" /> in scenes shot on Stage 8 at [[Elstree Studios]] between [[June 17]] and [[June 28]], [[1976]].<ref name="MakingOf">''[[The Making of Star Wars: The Definitive Story Behind the Original Film]]''</ref> The [[1996]] ''[[A New Hope Limited]]'' expansion set of the [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]] would later name the starfighter.<ref name="B4card" />

Inconsistencies exist relating to Black 4. [[1998]]'s ''[[Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' and [[2008]]'s ''[[The Complete Star Wars Encyclopedia]]'' claimed that DS-61-4 survived the Battle of Yavin, despite Black 4's onscreen destruction with DS-61-4 inside in ''A New Hope''.<ref name="swe">''[[Star Wars Encyclopedia]]''</ref><ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|I|212|DS-61-4}}</ref> Additionally, [[2002]]'s [[A New Hope (TCG)|''A New Hope'']] expansion of the ''[[Star Wars Trading Card Game]]'' used a film still of Black 4 to represent TIE Fighter [[DS-3-12]],<ref name="TCG">{{TCG|set=A New Hope|cardname=TIE Fighter DS-3-12|link=https://swtcg.com/Content/Images/Cards/ANH/TIE_Fighter_DS_3_12.webp?v=2}}</ref> while the [[2003]] [[Battle of Yavin (TCG)|''Battle of Yavin'']] set used film stills of Black 4 to represent TIE Fighters [[DS-55-2]]<ref name="TCG2">{{TCG|set=Battle of Yavin|cardname=TIE Fighter DS-55-2|link=https://swtcg.com/Content/Images/Cards/BOY/TIE_Fighter_DS_55_2.webp?v=2}}</ref> and [[DS-73-5]].<ref name="TCG3">{{TCG|set=Battle of Yavin|cardname=TIE Fighter DS-73-5|link=https://swtcg.com/Content/Images/Cards/BOY/TIE_Fighter_DS_73_5.webp?v=2}}</ref> This article, as well as other linking articles, treat DS-61-4 in Black 4 as the true identities of the TIE pilot and fighter from the ''A New Hope'' film, and treat the other designations as [[canon]] subjects separate from DS-61-4 and Black 4.

